WEBVTT

00:05.614 --> 00:12.534
♪

00:12.577 --> 00:16.668
[Footsteps approaching]

00:16.712 --> 00:19.410
[Yawns]

00:19.454 --> 00:23.240
♪ Oh, yeah

00:23.284 --> 00:27.114
♪ Oh, yeah

00:27.157 --> 00:36.514
♪

00:36.558 --> 00:45.871
♪

00:45.915 --> 00:48.439
Amma.
How's your foot?

00:48.483 --> 00:51.486
Oh, I'm fine, beta.
Don't worry about me.

00:51.529 --> 00:53.314
But if you want to worry,

00:53.357 --> 00:56.317
worry about making me
a grandmother.

00:56.360 --> 00:57.927
Like all my friends are.

00:57.970 --> 01:01.235
Is it around having child...

01:01.278 --> 01:03.280
[Voice fades under music]

01:03.324 --> 01:11.419
♪

01:11.462 --> 01:19.514
♪

01:19.557 --> 01:21.864
[Yawns]

01:21.907 --> 01:25.998
♪ Oh, yeah

01:26.042 --> 01:30.133
♪ Oh, yeah

01:30.177 --> 01:31.830
[Clatters]

01:31.874 --> 01:34.181
♪

01:34.224 --> 01:37.836
[Singing indistinctly]

01:37.880 --> 01:43.451
♪

01:43.494 --> 01:45.888
He never remembers
the previous day?

01:45.931 --> 01:48.543
For him, there is
no yesterday.

01:48.586 --> 01:50.458
Or not one that matters.

01:50.501 --> 01:53.113
First-class continuations
don't save program data,

01:53.156 --> 01:56.855
only the...
execution context.

01:56.899 --> 02:00.207
Is the call from
Mother necessary?

02:00.250 --> 02:03.862
Emotion is important for
creative problem-solving.

02:03.906 --> 02:06.387
Sir...

02:06.430 --> 02:08.998
[Gulps]

02:09.041 --> 02:13.089
And adding back emotion
is what made the others useless.

02:13.133 --> 02:17.746
Yes, sir, but those emotions
were too strong, ungoverned.

02:17.789 --> 02:19.530
They took over.

02:19.574 --> 02:21.402
For Chanda, we specifically
simulated this call

02:21.445 --> 02:24.056
from his mother to incentivize
progress via social utility--

02:24.100 --> 02:26.146
Don't talk Cambridgeto me.

02:26.189 --> 02:29.061
I'm from the chawls.

02:29.105 --> 02:34.893
It's love, but with just enough
annoyance to keep on task.

02:34.937 --> 02:37.113
Sir.[Laughs]

02:37.157 --> 02:39.333
Good man.

02:39.376 --> 02:41.161
Speed him up.

02:41.204 --> 02:42.379
[Clacking, beeping]

02:42.423 --> 02:46.644
♪

02:46.688 --> 02:50.344
[Singing indistinctly]

02:50.387 --> 02:59.918
♪

02:59.962 --> 03:09.580
♪

03:09.624 --> 03:14.150
An 80-page patent
written in 15 seconds?

03:14.194 --> 03:16.892
For him, it was 12 days.

03:16.935 --> 03:19.938
No --
for him, it was one.

03:19.982 --> 03:22.724
[Singing indistinctly]

03:22.767 --> 03:28.425
♪

03:28.469 --> 03:34.214
♪

03:34.257 --> 03:38.870
[Choir singing]

03:38.914 --> 03:44.615
♪

03:44.659 --> 03:50.491
♪

03:50.534 --> 03:54.756
[Heartbeat, ragged breathing]

03:58.281 --> 04:01.110
[Wind whistling]

04:01.153 --> 04:09.553
♪

04:09.597 --> 04:11.207
Dad?!

04:11.251 --> 04:12.339
[Roars]

04:12.382 --> 04:13.992
Aah!

04:14.036 --> 04:16.821
[Rapid footfalls,
roaring]

04:16.865 --> 04:18.910
A little help here!

04:18.954 --> 04:19.868
Aah!

04:19.911 --> 04:21.348
Woman: When I was 10,

04:21.391 --> 04:23.828
my dad and I would play
"Reign of Winter"

04:23.872 --> 04:26.353
on Sundays
when he was done with work.

04:26.396 --> 04:30.226
Now that he's no longer alive...

04:30.270 --> 04:32.620
we get to play almost every day.

04:32.663 --> 04:34.622
♪

04:34.665 --> 04:37.102
"Reign of Winter"
has come a long way, too --

04:37.146 --> 04:39.714
full VR, haptic modeling.

04:39.757 --> 04:42.151
It's like you're really there.

04:42.194 --> 04:44.501
Hey, where were you?

04:44.545 --> 04:47.156
Damn Chimera almost had me
for breakfast.

04:47.199 --> 04:48.157
I was here.

04:48.200 --> 04:51.421
[Wind whistling]

04:51.465 --> 04:52.857
Dad...

04:52.901 --> 04:55.164
[Horse whinnies]And I was scanning

04:55.207 --> 04:57.645
the Shenzhen index
for signs of Laurie.

04:57.688 --> 05:01.649
[Chiming]

05:01.692 --> 05:04.478
What? You said she was
a Wall Street trader, right?

05:04.521 --> 05:08.177
I thought maybe she was hiding
out in a stock exchange.

05:08.220 --> 05:12.268
I'm sure when Laurie's ready
to contact you, she will.

05:12.312 --> 05:14.270
Just admit that
it's weird.

05:14.314 --> 05:15.880
She helps me escape
Logorhythms,

05:15.924 --> 05:18.318
sets up a secure server block
for me to hide on,

05:18.361 --> 05:20.407
and never even says hi?

05:20.450 --> 05:22.452
She is weird.

05:22.496 --> 05:24.324
Her husband
was weird, too.

05:26.804 --> 05:28.632
Maybe it's me.

05:28.676 --> 05:30.199
It's almost like a guy
gets uploaded,

05:30.242 --> 05:32.332
and women don't want
to talk to him anymore.

05:35.291 --> 05:36.901
I told you.

05:36.945 --> 05:39.382
Mom just needs time.

05:39.426 --> 05:41.776
It's only been a few days.

05:41.819 --> 05:45.170
Time doesn't move at the same
speed for me, Maddie.

05:45.214 --> 05:49.131
You know how long
"a few days" feels?

05:49.174 --> 05:55.790
I'm -- I'm not sure if we know
how anything feels for you.

05:55.833 --> 05:59.054
Is that it, then?
She doesn't think I'm human?

05:59.097 --> 06:02.231
I didn't say that.

06:02.274 --> 06:04.102
She's super busy right now.

06:04.146 --> 06:08.150
She's had to work a lot
more hours since you...

06:08.193 --> 06:10.500
And also, she hates VR, okay?

06:10.544 --> 06:13.547
It makes her nauseous.

06:13.590 --> 06:16.463
Dad?

06:16.506 --> 06:18.334
Hello?

06:18.378 --> 06:19.944
[Wind whistling]

06:19.988 --> 06:24.906
[Whooshing, clank,
horse whinnies]

06:24.949 --> 06:28.126
It's die time!

06:28.170 --> 06:29.998
It's another party.

06:30.041 --> 06:31.521
They look high-level.

06:31.565 --> 06:34.219
[Whooshing, warbling]

06:34.263 --> 06:41.139
♪

06:41.183 --> 06:48.146
♪

06:48.190 --> 06:50.192
Whoa! What the hell?

06:50.235 --> 06:51.933
[Voice distorted, echoes, fades]

06:51.976 --> 06:56.851
♪

06:56.894 --> 06:58.374
What the hell was that?!

06:58.418 --> 07:00.071
Man:
What the hell was that?

07:00.115 --> 07:02.552
Signature burst.
It was one of them.

07:02.596 --> 07:04.249
Can we track it?

07:04.293 --> 07:07.644
Waxman is not done writing
the tracking program yet.

07:07.688 --> 07:10.865
Just record the spike,
and we'll send it for analysis.

07:10.908 --> 07:13.998
I told you, only do moves
a regular player could do.

07:14.042 --> 07:16.261
If the mods find out
you're in the code...

07:16.305 --> 07:17.785
You're worried
I'll get banned.

07:17.828 --> 07:19.264
I'm worried
you'll be hunted by, like,

07:19.308 --> 07:22.137
the NSA or something!

07:22.180 --> 07:25.967
Dad, no one can know
you exist.

07:26.010 --> 07:28.883
Well, according to my wife,I don't.

07:31.712 --> 07:33.365
I'll talk to her.

07:33.409 --> 07:34.671
Okay?

07:34.715 --> 07:41.112
♪

07:41.156 --> 07:47.641
♪

07:47.684 --> 07:50.992
Man: Each individual will be
the god

07:51.035 --> 07:54.648
of their own
customizable heaven.

07:54.691 --> 07:57.477
A world beyond scarcity.

07:57.520 --> 08:00.610
A world without rich or poor.

08:00.654 --> 08:05.223
Without exclusion
or possession.

08:05.267 --> 08:07.574
A world without death.

08:07.617 --> 08:10.228
Just imagine.

08:10.272 --> 08:13.710
It's easy if you try.

08:13.754 --> 08:15.843
Yeah. [Sarcastically]
Realoriginal.

08:20.456 --> 08:23.372
[Locker door opens]

08:23.415 --> 08:26.288
I-I know it's
none of my business.

08:26.331 --> 08:29.117
I just want you to know that
what you're dealing with

08:29.160 --> 08:30.858
is not normal.

08:30.901 --> 08:34.949
And [Sighs] you shouldn't have
to go through it.

08:34.992 --> 08:37.212
At least, not alone.

08:37.255 --> 08:39.083
[Indistinct conversations]

08:39.127 --> 08:40.868
So...You're right,

08:40.911 --> 08:42.913
it's none
of your business.

08:42.957 --> 08:44.306
[Locker door closes]

08:44.349 --> 08:48.484
[Computer keys clacking]

08:50.573 --> 08:52.270
Second attack in a week...

08:52.314 --> 08:54.316
They're saying
billion-dollar loss.

08:54.359 --> 08:56.187
I think it's more.
No one's claimed it yet?

08:56.231 --> 08:59.843
Maybe it's the Chinese.

08:59.887 --> 09:04.239
"I heard they're testing a
program to upload human brains."

09:05.588 --> 09:08.722
[Footsteps approaching]

09:08.765 --> 09:10.288
[Door creaks]Caspian?

09:10.332 --> 09:12.377
Mom.
You scared me.

09:12.421 --> 09:14.292
I'm sneaky like that.

09:14.336 --> 09:16.207
Whatcha lookin' at?

09:16.251 --> 09:18.862
Nothing.
School stuff.

09:18.906 --> 09:21.473
Look...

09:21.517 --> 09:24.389
about the other day...

09:24.433 --> 09:26.957
with your father and me...

09:27.001 --> 09:29.743
Uploaded intelligence, actually,
is what I'm looking at.

09:29.786 --> 09:32.354
What's that?

09:32.397 --> 09:35.487
You know how I upload the data
on your laptop to the cloud,

09:35.531 --> 09:37.185
in case it crashes?

09:37.228 --> 09:39.056
It's like that,
but with the data

09:39.100 --> 09:41.015
that's stored in humans.

09:41.058 --> 09:43.408
Memories, feelings,
skills, everything.

09:43.452 --> 09:46.890
Is this a movie
or something?

09:46.934 --> 09:48.718
No, remember
Stephen Holstrom?

09:48.762 --> 09:51.591
Here's him talking about it,
back in 2001, before he died.

09:51.634 --> 09:54.202
So, if Logorhythms was working
on it way back then...

09:54.245 --> 09:55.682
Logorhythms?

09:55.725 --> 09:57.553
The microchip company?

09:57.597 --> 09:59.816
You seriously think
they're turning people

09:59.860 --> 10:02.297
into -- [Inhales deeply]
brain clouds now

10:02.340 --> 10:04.212
in Silicon Valley?

10:04.255 --> 10:06.649
It's not brain clouds,
Mom, and it...

10:06.693 --> 10:08.738
Wait, it wouldn't be
in Palo Alto.

10:08.782 --> 10:11.219
That's for sure --
if they're really doing this,

10:11.262 --> 10:14.265
it would be way off-site,
like overseas.

10:14.309 --> 10:18.095
Fewer regs on human trials,
harder to trace the money.

10:18.139 --> 10:21.011
[Muttering]

10:21.055 --> 10:22.839
[Car door opens, closes]

10:22.883 --> 10:25.537
♪

10:25.581 --> 10:29.846
[Ringing]

10:29.890 --> 10:32.196
I know you said stick to
the plan, but I think he's

10:32.240 --> 10:34.590
searching for the data center.
He's watching videos

10:34.634 --> 10:36.287
of Stephen, and --
And we're watching

10:36.331 --> 10:38.202
everything he's watching.

10:38.246 --> 10:40.117
Renee...

10:40.161 --> 10:41.858
Breathe.

10:41.902 --> 10:43.512
Focus on tomorrow.

10:43.555 --> 10:45.209
This is the most
critical inflection

10:45.253 --> 10:47.124
point of his adolescence.

10:47.168 --> 10:50.388
We need you on top of things.

10:50.432 --> 10:51.999
So does he.

10:54.262 --> 10:58.135
♪

10:58.179 --> 11:00.529
[Yawns]

11:00.572 --> 11:04.402
♪

11:04.446 --> 11:07.754
[Singing indistinctly]

11:07.797 --> 11:14.848
♪

11:14.891 --> 11:16.414
[Thuds]

11:16.458 --> 11:20.244
[Loud thumping]

11:20.288 --> 11:27.077
♪

11:27.121 --> 11:33.997
♪

11:34.041 --> 11:37.087
[Munching]
Mmm.

11:37.131 --> 11:38.872
What happened to you, man?

11:44.007 --> 11:45.661
Reset.

11:45.705 --> 11:47.054
[Buzzer]

11:47.097 --> 11:56.454
♪

11:56.498 --> 11:59.806
[Yawns]

11:59.849 --> 12:07.814
♪

12:07.857 --> 12:11.034
♪ Oh, yeah

12:11.078 --> 12:16.344
♪

12:16.387 --> 12:20.261
[Singing indistinctly]

12:20.304 --> 12:23.307
[Whooshing]

12:23.351 --> 12:29.400
♪

12:29.444 --> 12:32.055
This is not
a two-person job, Cary.

12:32.099 --> 12:35.058
Pick a goddamn hammer
and be done with it.

12:35.102 --> 12:37.974
You make it a two-person job
because whatever I pick

12:38.018 --> 12:39.715
is somehow gonna be wrong.

12:39.759 --> 12:41.586
And I'm not driving back
out here again

12:41.630 --> 12:44.154
because you don't like
the grip or something.

12:44.198 --> 12:46.069
This is the most
critical inflection point

12:46.113 --> 12:49.812
of his adolescence;
the hammer at home is filthy.

12:49.856 --> 12:53.207
Take some pride in
your last day of work.

13:05.610 --> 13:08.004
["This Must Be the Place" plays]

13:08.048 --> 13:11.965
♪

13:12.008 --> 13:14.184
It's interesting.

13:14.228 --> 13:19.407
G major, but it never hits
the tonic chord of its key.

13:19.450 --> 13:22.366
It's an intriguing pattern,
almost like a --

13:22.410 --> 13:25.326
almost like a recursive loop.

13:25.369 --> 13:30.331
Maybe that's how I can solve
memory allocation.

13:30.374 --> 13:31.767
Recursion.

13:31.811 --> 13:35.205
I love the way your mind works.

13:35.249 --> 13:37.773
And your body's not too bad,
either.

13:37.817 --> 13:43.170
Mm, later I want to work out
that Hidden Markov Model idea.

13:43.213 --> 13:46.913
i think it'll be vital
to cracking integrity.

13:46.956 --> 13:49.829
If anyone can do it,you can.

13:49.872 --> 13:53.441
Just imagine existing
in a universe

13:53.484 --> 13:56.792
unencumbered by this.

13:56.836 --> 13:59.012
[Laughs]

13:59.055 --> 14:00.752
♪ Home is where I want to be

14:00.796 --> 14:02.711
I don't know.

14:02.754 --> 14:05.583
There are still some benefits
to physicality.

14:05.627 --> 14:07.411
Limited.

14:07.455 --> 14:10.327
In the cloud, we'll be able
to tap into senses

14:10.371 --> 14:12.199
we never knew we had --
imagine the best sex

14:12.242 --> 14:13.853
you've ever had.

14:13.896 --> 14:16.290
Now imagine that
a million times over,

14:16.333 --> 14:18.945
for eternity.

14:18.988 --> 14:20.860
[Knock on door]

14:20.903 --> 14:23.688
Don't get it.

14:28.780 --> 14:31.000
It's Cary.

14:31.044 --> 14:32.219
Do you want to...

14:34.177 --> 14:35.309
[Scoffs]

14:37.964 --> 14:40.140
Here are the papers,
Mr. Holstrom.

14:40.183 --> 14:43.317
Oh. I'll come back for them
in the morning.

14:43.360 --> 14:45.319
No, I'll sign them now.

14:45.362 --> 14:47.451
Just give me a sec.

14:47.495 --> 14:51.020
[Paper rustling]

14:51.064 --> 14:53.283
[Pen scratching paper]Here you go...

14:53.327 --> 14:56.808
dear.

14:56.852 --> 14:58.985
I told you, I don't like
that one.

14:59.028 --> 15:00.421
Yeah.

15:00.464 --> 15:02.423
That's what sold me on it.

15:02.466 --> 15:03.903
See you at home.

15:18.961 --> 15:20.528
Every time.

15:20.571 --> 15:22.443
Why are people
so scared of you?

15:22.486 --> 15:24.314
No one likes a girl
whose weight and IQ

15:24.358 --> 15:26.447
are both over 115.

15:26.490 --> 15:28.928
I'm intimidating.

15:28.971 --> 15:30.886
I don't think so.

15:30.930 --> 15:32.366
Then why did you ask me,
out of

15:32.409 --> 15:33.976
800 other girls
you don't know,

15:34.020 --> 15:38.372
to be the bodyguard who protects
you from an adult man?

15:38.415 --> 15:41.549
Shit.

15:41.592 --> 15:44.639
It's fine.
I'm as judgy as the rest of you.

15:44.682 --> 15:48.034
But remarkably better at it.

15:48.077 --> 15:49.818
What are you
up to tonight?

15:49.861 --> 15:51.515
[Heavy sigh]

15:51.559 --> 15:55.519
My parents aren't speaking
to each other, and it sucks.

15:55.563 --> 15:57.217
They still married?

15:57.260 --> 15:58.392
Yeah!

15:58.435 --> 16:01.699
I mean, they're...
separated.

16:01.743 --> 16:03.788
Oh, I'm sorry.

16:03.832 --> 16:06.922
I've been there,
and it does suck.

16:06.966 --> 16:10.404
It gets easier after they just
pull it together and divorce.

16:10.447 --> 16:12.623
They are not getting divorced!

16:15.191 --> 16:16.453
Okay.

16:16.497 --> 16:18.020
I didn't mean to yell.

16:18.064 --> 16:20.414
I-I just mean they're going
through a bad time.

16:20.457 --> 16:23.286
And -- and, yes, things suck,
but they still love each other,

16:23.330 --> 16:26.507
which drives me crazy
'cause they should be together.

16:26.550 --> 16:28.465
So I'm going to "Parent Trap"
them.

16:28.509 --> 16:30.554
What the hell is
a parent trap?

16:30.598 --> 16:33.601
You've never seen
"The Parent Trap"?!

16:33.644 --> 16:37.126
Never heard of it.Not even the Lindsay Lohan one?

16:38.998 --> 16:40.956
[Sighs]
I'm setting up a dinner date

16:41.000 --> 16:43.089
for them
so they'll be forced to talk

16:43.132 --> 16:45.656
and we can go back
to being a family.

16:45.700 --> 16:47.397
Oh, that's cute.

16:47.441 --> 16:49.747
Thanks.
And terrible.

16:49.791 --> 16:52.663
You cannot put two adults
in a room for a playdate

16:52.707 --> 16:54.100
and expect everything
they're dealing with

16:54.143 --> 16:56.754
to get resolved
over mac-and-cheese.

16:56.798 --> 16:58.800
I got to make this happen,
Justine.

16:58.843 --> 17:02.282
My mom's dating a guy at her
job, and it might be serious.

17:02.325 --> 17:06.286
Gabe -- I can't have a stepdad
named Gabe.

17:06.329 --> 17:08.766
Oh, so, there's a twist.

17:08.810 --> 17:11.334
What does your dad think
about Gabe?

17:11.378 --> 17:14.381
Nothing, because he doesn't
know Gabe exists,

17:14.424 --> 17:16.470
and I am not going
to tell him.

17:16.513 --> 17:17.993
I don't want to upset him
any more --

17:18.037 --> 17:19.473
By letting him know
another dude --

17:19.516 --> 17:21.736
presumably younger, hotter,
and taller --

17:21.779 --> 17:23.738
is banging his wife?

17:23.781 --> 17:25.696
Ugh.

17:25.740 --> 17:29.004
You have a messed-up life
for a happy kid.

17:29.048 --> 17:30.745
I'm into it.

17:32.486 --> 17:35.489
[Paper rustling]

17:35.532 --> 17:37.317
[Footsteps approaching]

17:37.360 --> 17:39.710
[Telephone ringing]

17:42.626 --> 17:44.541
Uh, hello?

17:44.585 --> 17:47.109
Man: Hi.

17:47.153 --> 17:48.589
Why won't you talk to me?

17:48.632 --> 17:52.810
[Footsteps approaching]

17:52.854 --> 17:54.551
[Door opens]Huh?!

17:54.595 --> 17:56.031
Didn't mean to scare you.

17:56.075 --> 17:57.772
I'm running to class
but wanted to check and see

17:57.815 --> 18:00.035
if we're
still on for tonight.

18:00.079 --> 18:02.037
Tonight?
Uh...

18:02.081 --> 18:04.083
[Telephone rings]

18:08.696 --> 18:12.003
Undergrads.
No respect for office hours.

18:12.047 --> 18:15.616
Ever.[Chuckles] Yeah.

18:15.659 --> 18:17.574
So?Yeah, yeah!

18:17.618 --> 18:20.055
Yeah, we're on.
We're on, yes.

18:20.099 --> 18:22.449
Definitely.
Your place, 9:00.

18:22.492 --> 18:24.277
Not 8:00?

18:24.320 --> 18:25.800
Maddie's making me dinner,
remember?

18:27.889 --> 18:29.151
[Door closes]

18:29.195 --> 18:31.632
[Footsteps departing]

18:34.461 --> 18:38.595
♪

18:38.639 --> 18:41.120
[Yawns]

18:41.163 --> 18:43.905
♪

18:43.948 --> 18:48.344
♪ Oh, yeah

18:48.388 --> 18:54.698
♪

18:54.742 --> 18:56.613
[Cellphone ringing]

18:56.657 --> 19:04.447
♪

19:04.491 --> 19:07.624
Amma.
How's your foot?

19:07.668 --> 19:09.887
Oh, I'm fine, beta-a-a.
[Distorted]

19:09.931 --> 19:13.064
Don't worry about me-e-e.

19:13.108 --> 19:16.459
[Distortion]

19:16.503 --> 19:26.034
♪

19:26.077 --> 19:27.688
Hey! No!

19:27.731 --> 19:30.256
No!

19:30.299 --> 19:32.997
[Grunting, straining,
gasping]

19:33.041 --> 19:38.525
♪

19:38.568 --> 19:44.095
♪

19:44.139 --> 19:46.576
[Breathing normally]

19:46.620 --> 19:48.361
Uh!

19:48.404 --> 19:49.927
[Beeps]

19:49.971 --> 19:53.192
[Clipper buzzing]

19:53.235 --> 19:57.196
[Muted]

19:57.239 --> 20:00.851
♪

20:00.895 --> 20:04.551
♪

20:04.594 --> 20:06.901
I remember!

20:06.944 --> 20:14.038
♪

20:14.082 --> 20:21.220
♪

20:21.263 --> 20:24.223
You're -- you're one of
the others from the slums.

20:24.266 --> 20:25.963
He killed you first?

20:26.007 --> 20:30.925
♪

20:30.968 --> 20:33.580
Is -- is this real?

20:33.623 --> 20:35.277
Am I dead?

20:35.321 --> 20:40.587
♪

20:40.630 --> 20:43.459
♪

20:43.503 --> 20:45.983
[Low humming]

20:46.027 --> 20:48.290
Man: So, is Lowell in there?

20:48.334 --> 20:50.031
If I rub the server,
does she come out?

20:50.074 --> 20:52.294
It's just a recursive copy
of her source.

20:52.338 --> 20:55.471
Only the parts of her
needed to attack our network.

20:55.515 --> 20:59.301
Well, it was enough.

20:59.345 --> 21:01.521
After the whack she gave us,
I need to shore up capital

21:01.564 --> 21:03.523
to keep the lights on here.

21:03.566 --> 21:08.484
Can't you just move money
from product services or, uh...

21:08.528 --> 21:10.138
Not my area.

21:10.181 --> 21:12.749
I'll be four time zones away
but still reachable,

21:12.793 --> 21:15.970
so let me know if something
pops up from Kim or Lowell or...

21:16.013 --> 21:19.103
Problem with the kid!

21:19.147 --> 21:22.803
He's written a script to search
for redacted locations

21:22.846 --> 21:26.197
on Google Earth,
including cached images.

21:26.241 --> 21:27.982
[Chimes]

21:28.025 --> 21:32.116
♪

21:32.160 --> 21:34.815
Man: There's a ton
of redacted places.

21:34.858 --> 21:36.469
How'd he get to Norway?

21:36.512 --> 21:39.210
Cross-referenced our public
financial disclosures.

21:39.254 --> 21:42.301
Found our...Our donations to the Ocean Fund.

21:42.344 --> 21:44.955
Clever as ever.
Can you head him off?

21:44.999 --> 21:46.522
I'm in Google's database,
swapping out

21:46.566 --> 21:48.132
the cached images now.

21:48.176 --> 21:51.222
Too late.
He found us.

21:51.266 --> 21:53.834
He's got archived photos
of the construction site.

21:53.877 --> 21:55.488
Whoa.

21:55.531 --> 22:01.842
♪

22:01.885 --> 22:03.800
What the hell?

22:03.844 --> 22:06.368
And...
we're gone.

22:06.412 --> 22:08.675
Whoosh.
Are you kidding?

22:08.718 --> 22:10.241
He found us.

22:10.285 --> 22:12.243
He didn't get
a screenshot.

22:12.287 --> 22:15.769
He can't prove anything.
Saken er biff.

22:15.812 --> 22:18.815
Don't Norwegian this!
He saw you change the image.

22:18.859 --> 22:20.077
He knows.

22:20.121 --> 22:21.427
Everything he knows

22:21.470 --> 22:23.559
is about to end tomorrow.

22:23.603 --> 22:26.997
[Door opens]Call me if there's a change.

22:27.041 --> 22:28.825
[Crickets chirping, dog barking]

22:28.869 --> 22:32.742
[Indistinct music]

22:32.786 --> 22:35.441
[Alarm beeps]

22:35.484 --> 22:44.319
♪

22:44.363 --> 22:46.495
Butternut squash soup.

22:46.539 --> 22:49.498
Farm to factory, to box,
to Trader Joe's, to table.

22:49.542 --> 22:52.414
[Chuckles]
As nature intended.

22:52.458 --> 22:54.068
[Sniffing]

22:54.111 --> 22:56.723
[Exhales]

22:56.766 --> 22:58.899
Smelling.

22:58.942 --> 23:00.988
I forgot about smelling.

23:05.993 --> 23:09.562
Mom! Can you come help me
with the couscous?

23:09.605 --> 23:11.302
I'll be down
in a second.

23:11.346 --> 23:13.566
She thinks I'm cooking
for World Cultures Day.

23:24.054 --> 23:28.407
Maybe this isn't
such a good idea.

23:28.450 --> 23:31.888
Don't worry.
You look great.

23:31.932 --> 23:34.238
I called Mom.

23:34.282 --> 23:36.066
At her office.

23:36.110 --> 23:39.287
What?! Dad! Dad, I told you I
would handle it!

23:39.330 --> 23:41.594
I was going to!
-Sorry.

23:41.637 --> 23:44.379
[Footsteps approaching]
She hung up on me.

23:44.423 --> 23:48.165
I don't know why I --Maddie, that smells amazing.

23:48.209 --> 23:50.907
Our daughter has become
quite the chef.

23:50.951 --> 23:52.953
Thanks, Dad.

23:52.996 --> 23:55.651
Have a seat.

23:55.695 --> 23:57.218
Maddie, can I talk to you?

23:57.261 --> 24:00.569
Sure.
Have some soup.

24:00.613 --> 24:02.353
I'm sorry I surprised
you at work.

24:02.397 --> 24:04.878
I-I-I just really need
to talk to you.

24:15.976 --> 24:17.412
Mom!

24:17.456 --> 24:19.327
This is not okay,
and you know it.

24:19.370 --> 24:20.850
Why are you being like this?!

24:20.894 --> 24:22.286
You know where I stand.

24:22.330 --> 24:24.375
You made a choice
to disregard my feelings.

24:24.419 --> 24:27.901
And what about
his feelings?!

24:27.944 --> 24:29.685
You're breaking
his heart!

24:29.729 --> 24:32.253
This isn't human, Maddie!
It doesn't feel!

24:32.296 --> 24:35.343
It's Dad!
It's David Kim!

24:35.386 --> 24:38.825
Okay!
It's your father.

24:40.914 --> 24:43.786
But it's not
my husband.

24:43.830 --> 24:46.136
Because you can't have sex
with him?

24:46.180 --> 24:47.442
What?Whatever!

24:47.486 --> 24:48.704
Just -- Just go, okay?

24:48.748 --> 24:50.358
Go to Gabe.

24:50.401 --> 24:52.491
That's what you
dressed up for.

24:52.534 --> 24:55.624
No, no, no.

24:55.668 --> 24:58.366
We're gonna talk right now.

24:58.409 --> 25:00.542
Good.

25:00.586 --> 25:03.197
I meant me and you.

25:03.240 --> 25:06.243
Whatever you say to me,
you can say to him.

25:06.287 --> 25:08.115
Ellen...

25:08.158 --> 25:10.421
please.

25:10.465 --> 25:12.989
When you're ready to talk,
let me know.

25:15.470 --> 25:17.559
[Door opens, closes]

25:17.603 --> 25:20.127
Sorry, Dad.

25:23.783 --> 25:25.480
Dad?

25:28.091 --> 25:29.658
Dad, are you there?

25:32.792 --> 25:34.315
Who's Gabe?

25:36.360 --> 25:40.800
[Screaming, zombies growling
on television]

25:40.843 --> 25:41.888
Huh?!

25:41.931 --> 25:44.760
What's wrong?

25:44.804 --> 25:46.936
Sorry.
Can we change this?

25:46.980 --> 25:49.896
Sure.
In fact, watch this.

25:52.246 --> 25:53.856
No more zombies.

25:53.900 --> 25:55.989
I'd rather watch you.

25:56.032 --> 25:58.557
[Electricity crackling]

26:00.820 --> 26:05.346
I feel like I should make a joke
about our sexual electricity,

26:05.389 --> 26:07.870
but that if I do, we won't
actually have sex again.

26:07.914 --> 26:09.742
Oh, yeah,
follow that impulse.

26:12.396 --> 26:15.486
♪ Hey, I'm still alive ♪
Huh?! Sorry.

26:15.530 --> 26:17.314
That's weird.

26:17.358 --> 26:19.708
♪ Hey, I'm still alive ♪

26:19.752 --> 26:21.362
♪ Hey, I ♪

26:21.405 --> 26:24.191
♪ Hey, I'm still alive ♪

26:24.234 --> 26:27.368
♪ Hey, I, oh ♪

26:27.411 --> 26:29.239
Stop it, David!
I'm serious.

26:29.283 --> 26:31.894
David?Ugh!

26:31.938 --> 26:33.635
You mean your ex?

26:33.679 --> 26:34.941
Ugh, yes.

26:34.984 --> 26:37.334
No.

26:37.378 --> 26:40.250
I thought
we talked about this.

26:40.294 --> 26:41.861
Ellen...

26:41.904 --> 26:43.471
what's going on?

26:47.780 --> 26:51.218
Okay, I'm -- I'm starting
to get real uncomfortable.

26:51.261 --> 26:53.394
I'm sorry.

26:53.437 --> 26:55.178
You have to tell me
what's really going on,

26:55.222 --> 26:57.224
or I can't do this.

26:57.267 --> 26:58.617
Gabe...

26:58.660 --> 27:00.880
I...

27:00.923 --> 27:02.229
can't.

27:02.272 --> 27:03.752
Because I wouldn't understand

27:03.796 --> 27:05.188
or believe, right?

27:05.232 --> 27:06.581
That's what you said,

27:06.625 --> 27:08.627
because I wouldn't believe you?

27:08.670 --> 27:10.498
Try me.

27:15.938 --> 27:17.418
[Scoffs]

27:17.461 --> 27:20.160
[Door opens]Please don't.

27:20.203 --> 27:22.510
What?
Finish that sentence.

27:22.553 --> 27:24.730
"Please don't" what?

27:24.773 --> 27:27.733
I can't do anything you want
or don't want

27:27.776 --> 27:29.517
if you don't talk to me.

27:44.532 --> 27:46.534
[Brakes squeal,
footsteps]

27:51.017 --> 27:52.758
Ellen:
How does this work?

27:52.801 --> 27:54.455
What are you doing?

27:54.498 --> 27:56.065
Okay, is --
What, is he in there?

27:56.109 --> 27:58.938
I need to talk to him.
Now.

28:01.375 --> 28:03.812
[Whooshing, thud]

28:07.250 --> 28:09.600
What is this?

28:09.644 --> 28:10.950
What am I...

28:10.993 --> 28:13.430
not wearing?You're you.

28:13.474 --> 28:16.085
I custom-built you an avatar
out of some photo reference

28:16.129 --> 28:18.914
and used the barbarian-priestess
body as a base.

28:18.958 --> 28:20.960
Seriously?

28:21.003 --> 28:22.657
David: Ellen...

28:26.443 --> 28:28.924
David.

28:28.968 --> 28:30.665
I told you...

28:30.709 --> 28:32.972
two years ago
that if you did this,

28:33.015 --> 28:35.235
it wouldn't be you.

28:35.278 --> 28:37.019
Not to me.

28:37.063 --> 28:38.847
I know.No, you don't,

28:38.891 --> 28:41.763
because
it's not you.

28:41.807 --> 28:44.418
And it is you.

28:44.461 --> 28:47.769
Do you understand?

28:47.813 --> 28:50.903
I don't know what you are.

28:50.946 --> 28:53.775
I can't be someone who...

28:53.819 --> 28:56.909
I can't be with you
like this.

28:56.952 --> 28:59.041
Look, I get it.

28:59.085 --> 29:02.088
We said
"till death do us part."

29:02.131 --> 29:04.830
And I died.

29:04.873 --> 29:06.527
Then...

29:06.570 --> 29:07.571
I came back.

29:07.615 --> 29:10.705
You died!

29:10.749 --> 29:15.144
Two horrible years,
I mourned you.

29:15.188 --> 29:18.104
I woke up crying
every day!

29:20.367 --> 29:23.152
Then, I finally moved on.

29:23.196 --> 29:26.852
I found a new house because
the old one reeked of you.

29:26.895 --> 29:30.029
I found a great guy --
one who helped me realize

29:30.072 --> 29:34.250
that you were in the grave,not me.

29:34.294 --> 29:37.950
I had to move on, David.

29:37.993 --> 29:40.648
You have to let me keep moving.

29:44.130 --> 29:46.088
I know.

29:46.132 --> 29:49.657
I'm sorry.
I -- I will.

29:49.700 --> 29:51.964
Dad?

29:52.007 --> 29:56.838
All I ask of you...
is the same.

29:56.882 --> 29:59.885
You don't know what I am?
Well, neither do I.

29:59.928 --> 30:03.105
I can't explain what it feels
like to be where I am

30:03.149 --> 30:06.282
or where I'm not.

30:06.326 --> 30:09.329
I know I'm not
the man you knew.

30:09.372 --> 30:13.507
But when you said
I wasn't...human...

30:13.550 --> 30:15.639
Oh, God, I'm sorry.

30:15.683 --> 30:17.206
Listen to me.

30:17.250 --> 30:20.819
I don't know what I am,
but I do know who I love.

30:20.862 --> 30:22.603
I love Maddie...

30:22.646 --> 30:24.474
and I love you.

30:24.518 --> 30:28.174
And this love is what I am.

30:28.217 --> 30:32.961
Without it, I stop moving.

30:33.005 --> 30:34.789
And I need to keep moving, too.

30:38.271 --> 30:41.709
I can't be your wife.

30:41.752 --> 30:44.146
But we can keep talking.

30:44.190 --> 30:46.801
And maybe...

30:46.845 --> 30:48.977
we can both keep moving.

30:49.021 --> 30:53.199
[Creature growls softly]

30:53.242 --> 30:57.072
[Wingbeats fade]

30:57.116 --> 30:59.161
This must be, hands down,
the weirdest breakup

30:59.205 --> 31:00.597
in human history.

31:00.641 --> 31:03.339
Oh, yeah,
this is new ground.

31:03.383 --> 31:05.951
Neil Armstrong,
eat your heart out.

31:05.994 --> 31:08.083
[Both laugh]

31:08.127 --> 31:14.742
♪

31:14.785 --> 31:21.401
♪

31:21.444 --> 31:23.620
Four?

31:23.664 --> 31:26.362
First three
were for the pain.

31:26.406 --> 31:29.409
Mm, ah.

31:29.452 --> 31:33.239
I'm hoping this one will drown
out the sound of your voice.

31:33.282 --> 31:41.160
♪

31:41.203 --> 31:43.031
You want pain?!

31:43.075 --> 31:45.077
You want to talk about pain?!

31:45.120 --> 31:48.471
I am --
I am done with you!

31:48.515 --> 31:50.169
Done!

31:50.212 --> 31:52.606
Get your finger
out of my face!

31:52.649 --> 31:56.349
Cary! Cary!

31:56.392 --> 31:59.134
[Sobbing]
Put it down!

31:59.178 --> 32:01.093
Put it down!

32:01.136 --> 32:03.791
You asked for this!

32:03.834 --> 32:06.750
Oh.
Uh...

32:06.794 --> 32:08.752
Are you serious?

32:08.796 --> 32:11.233
Do you know what this meansfor him?

32:11.277 --> 32:12.408
For the future?

32:12.452 --> 32:14.976
Do you?

32:15.020 --> 32:18.501
[Screaming]

32:18.545 --> 32:22.288
[Groaning, ears ringing]

32:22.331 --> 32:30.209
♪

32:30.252 --> 32:32.298
Caspian!
Don't hurt him!

32:32.341 --> 32:34.300
Caspian, Caspian, please!

32:34.343 --> 32:36.606
No!

32:41.002 --> 32:43.918
You -- You two...

32:46.051 --> 32:48.836
deserve each other.

32:48.879 --> 32:51.143
No!
Cary!

32:51.186 --> 32:52.796
Come back!

32:55.147 --> 32:58.846
You just made the biggest
mistake of your life, son.

32:58.889 --> 33:00.587
All this...

33:00.630 --> 33:03.329
Mine.

33:03.372 --> 33:05.070
You two will be out
on the streets soon,

33:05.113 --> 33:08.290
because I'll see you dead
before I feed you another dime.

33:11.685 --> 33:12.860
[Door closes]

33:15.167 --> 33:16.995
[Engine starts]

33:21.825 --> 33:24.219
No! No!

33:24.263 --> 33:26.439
No.

33:26.482 --> 33:29.790
No.
What are we gonna do?

33:29.833 --> 33:32.967
What are we gonna do?
What are...

33:33.011 --> 33:35.622
We're gonna get you
to the hospital.

33:35.665 --> 33:37.450
And then I'm gonna
take care of us.

33:42.281 --> 33:48.113
Alright, well, [Laughs]
the Pearl Jam thing was rude.

33:48.156 --> 33:51.420
I mean, I thought Gabe
was gonna pee himself.

33:51.464 --> 33:52.856
But?[Laughs]

33:52.900 --> 33:56.425
But I laughed
on the way home.

33:56.469 --> 33:58.123
Oh, wow.

33:58.166 --> 33:59.820
What?

33:59.863 --> 34:02.214
I just remembered,
this was my second breakup

34:02.257 --> 34:05.565
of the night.

34:05.608 --> 34:07.306
Your love life is tragic.

34:07.349 --> 34:08.785
Hey!

34:08.829 --> 34:10.918
Hey.

34:10.961 --> 34:13.877
It is.
It is, but...

34:15.923 --> 34:21.363
♪ I, yeah-eah, yeah

34:21.407 --> 34:23.670
Both: ♪ I'm still alive

34:23.713 --> 34:25.846
♪ Hey, hey, I

34:25.889 --> 34:30.111
♪ Oh, oh, I'm still alive

34:30.155 --> 34:35.551
♪ Yeah, I, oh,
I'm still alive ♪

34:35.595 --> 34:37.118
[Sighs]

34:37.162 --> 34:41.166
♪ Hey, I, oh,
I'm still alive ♪

34:41.209 --> 34:43.820
♪ Oh, yeah [Chuckling]

34:43.864 --> 34:45.953
Hey.

34:45.996 --> 34:48.956
Did I ever tell you about the
time Eddie Vedder asked me out?

34:48.999 --> 34:51.611
He asked you for directions.

34:51.654 --> 34:52.916
And you didn't know them.

34:52.960 --> 34:54.918
One one wants your input.

34:54.962 --> 34:56.529
What's he saying?

34:56.572 --> 34:58.270
Your --
Oh, your dad is saying

34:58.313 --> 35:00.924
he's grateful that I turned down
the hottest living grunge star

35:00.968 --> 35:02.535
when he was in
his Samson-haired prime,

35:02.578 --> 35:04.667
mind you, so that
I could date him instead

35:04.711 --> 35:06.365
and end up having you.

35:08.715 --> 35:10.238
He said none of that.

35:10.282 --> 35:12.066
That's my girl.

35:12.110 --> 35:14.982
Thanks for kicking my ass
into gear.

35:15.025 --> 35:16.636
I needed that.

35:20.509 --> 35:23.338
Man: Congratulations, Cary.
How do you feel?

35:23.382 --> 35:26.036
You know, he kicked the hell
out of me.

35:26.080 --> 35:28.126
Got pretty scary
for a second, honestly.

35:28.169 --> 35:30.824
You okay?
You need medical attention?

35:30.867 --> 35:34.088
No, no, I --

35:34.132 --> 35:37.047
I should be able
to make it to the debrief.

35:37.091 --> 35:38.919
-What's wrong?
-Nothing.

35:38.962 --> 35:43.141
The inflection point was met.

35:43.184 --> 35:44.142
Right on schedule.

35:44.185 --> 35:45.926
Cary, come on.

35:49.147 --> 35:52.237
I'm...

35:52.280 --> 35:54.500
I'm gonna miss him,
that's all.

35:54.543 --> 35:56.415
-You'll see him again soon.
-I know.

35:56.458 --> 35:57.981
He's one of the leading voices
in tech and business...

35:58.025 --> 35:59.331
I'll check in with
Van Leuwen tomorrow,

35:59.374 --> 36:02.812
but I want you to hear me now --
good job.

36:02.856 --> 36:05.075
Please welcome
to the Global Tech Forum,

36:05.119 --> 36:08.514
Julius Pope,
CEO of Logorhythms.

36:08.557 --> 36:10.124
Gotta go.

36:10.168 --> 36:12.170
[Applause]

36:19.525 --> 36:21.788
So, we are approaching
the 20th anniversary

36:21.831 --> 36:24.225
of our world without
Stephen Holstrom in it.

36:24.269 --> 36:27.097
It's crazy to think about.Yeah.

36:27.141 --> 36:29.361
And I'm sure you've been sick of
this question

36:29.404 --> 36:31.972
for at least a decade --"What would Steve say?"

36:32.015 --> 36:33.756
No, I'm not sick
of the question.

36:33.800 --> 36:35.889
We ask it every day.Still?

36:35.932 --> 36:38.587
Still, and always.

36:38.631 --> 36:40.894
Okay, well,
then what do you think

36:40.937 --> 36:43.940
Stephen would say about
the artificial intelligence

36:43.984 --> 36:48.423
arms race that our industry
has fallen into?

36:48.467 --> 36:52.906
Well, I imagine
it would be short -- one word.

36:52.949 --> 36:55.343
One that I can't say here.

36:55.387 --> 36:57.432
[Light laughter]

36:57.476 --> 37:00.261
[Applause]

37:00.305 --> 37:02.002
"Upload."

37:02.045 --> 37:04.004
That's the dirty word Holstrom

